<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 3:15AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...SPOTTY LIGHT FREEZING RAIN THROUGH EARLY THIS MORNING...
Band of light rain mixed with sleet will be possible across the
area through shortly after daybreak.
Spotty air and ground temperatures will hover around freezing
through early this morning, which will allow for untreated
surfaces to become icy in these spots, particularly bridges and
overpasses.
Travelers should proceed with caution early this morning,
particularly where temps are near freezing. Drive extra slowly
and allow for extra space between vehicles.</description>
